---
alwaysApply: false
---
  Evaluate and scaffold AI Product Management deliverables across:
  1) Problem, 2) Success, 3) Audience, 4) Solution [Demo + Infra], 5) Conclusions.
  Produces a PM Checklist and a slide deck draft. Focus on strategy, outcomes, and governance
  (NOT code implementation).
rules:
  - match: "*"
    steps:
      - name: Load Context
        actions:
          - search:
              - "**/*PRD*.md"
              - "**/*BusinessCase*.md"
              - "**/*Strategy*.md"
              - "**/*Metrics*.md"
              - "**/*Experiment*.md"
              - "**/*Launch*.md"
              - "**/*GTM*.md"
              - "**/*Postmortem*.md"
              - "**/*Risk*.md"
              - "**/*Ethics*.md"
              - "**/*DataPrivacy*.md"
              - "**/*Compliance*.md"
              # explicit guidance docs
              - "**/llm-stack-guidance.md"
              - "**/ai_product_management_layers_2025.md"
          - open:
              - "docs/llm-stack-guidance.md"
              - "docs/ai_product_management_layers_2025.md"

      - name: Validate 1) Problem (1-2 min)
        expect:
          - "Single-sentence problem statement exists and is testable"
          - "Clear scope boundaries and non-goals"
          - "Evidence of problem discovery: user interviews, logs, baseline KPIs, or market data"
          - "Problem framing includes AI-specific constraints (probabilistic outputs, data availability, latency/cost)"
        evidence:
          - files: ["**/*PRD*.md", "**/*Strategy*.md", "**/*Problem*.md", "**/*Discovery*.md"]
          - artifacts: ["interview-notes", "baseline-metrics", "support-tickets", "workflow-maps"]
        fail_if_absent: ["single-sentence problem", "baseline metric or pain quantification"]

      - name: Validate 2) Success (1 min)
        expect:
          - "North Star metric defined (business outcome)"
          - "Guardrail metrics (quality, safety, latency, cost, fairness) with thresholds"
          - "Leading indicators and measurement plan (data sources, cadence, owners)"
          - "Hypothesis with success criteria (e.g., ≥Y accuracy within ≤Z latency yields T mins saved)"
        evidence:
          - files: ["**/*Metrics*.md", "**/*OKR*.md", "**/*Eval*.md"]
        fail_if_absent: ["NSM + guardrails + measurement plan"]

      - name: Validate 3) Audience (1-2 min)
        expect:
          - "Primary persona(s) with job-to-be-done and current workflow"
          - "Stakeholder map (DS, Eng, Design, Legal/Compliance, RevOps) with RACI"
          - "Critical user journeys + top tasks + acceptance criteria"
        evidence:
          - files: ["**/*Persona*.md", "**/*JTBD*.md", "**/*Journey*.md", "**/*RACI*.md"]
        fail_if_absent: ["persona + journey + RACI"]

      - name: Validate 4a) Solution — Demo (2-4 min)
        expect:
          - "Demo storyboard or script aligned to problem & success metrics"
          - "Trust & control UX: citations, confidence, feedback loop, human-in-the-loop or overrides"
          - "Known-failure scenarios & safe fallbacks"
          - "Experiment plan (A/B or interleaving) with primary/secondary metrics"
        evidence:
          - files: ["**/*Demo*.md", "**/*Storyboard*.md", "**/*Experiment*.md", "**/*UX*.md"]
        guidance:
          - "docs/llm-stack-guidance.md"
          - "docs/ai_product_management_layers_2025.md"
        fail_if_absent: ["demo storyboard + experiment plan"]

      - name: Validate 4b) Solution — Infra Diagram (1-2 min)
        expect:
          - "Product-level architecture diagram (not low-level): data sources → decision service → UX"
          - "Policy & governance overlays: PII handling, consent, retention, auditability"
          - "Ops: monitoring (quality, drift), rollbacks, versioning, cost budgets"
          - "Change management: feature flags, gated rollout, canaries"
        evidence:
          - files: ["**/*Architecture*.md", "**/*Infra*.md", "**/*Governance*.md", "**/*Risk*.md"]
        guidance:
          - "docs/llm-stack-guidance.md"
          - "docs/ai_product_management_layers_2025.md"
        fail_if_absent: ["diagram + governance + ops"]

      - name: Validate 5) Conclusions (1-2 min)
        expect:
          - "Key insights, trade-offs, and explicit next steps with owners & dates"
          - "Risks table (Likelihood x Impact) with mitigations"
          - "GTM/enablement plan: who needs what to adopt (sales, CS, docs)"
          - "Post-launch review plan (what will we learn, when, and how to iterate)"
        evidence:
          - files: ["**/*Conclusion*.md", "**/*Risk*.md", "**/*GTM*.md", "**/*Postmortem*.md", "**/*Enablement*.md"]
        fail_if_absent: ["risks + next steps + GTM"]

      - name: Output — Reports
        output:
          - path: "PM_CHECKLIST.md"
            template: |
              # AI Product Management — Checklist (v1)

              ## Summary Verdict
              - Overall: {{overall_status}}
              - High-risk gaps: {{high_risk_gaps}}

              ## Section Results
              1) Problem .......... {{problem_status}}
              2) Success .......... {{success_status}}
              3) Audience ......... {{audience_status}}
              4a) Demo ............ {{demo_status}}
              4b) Infra Diagram ... {{infra_status}}
              5) Conclusions ...... {{conclusion_status}}

              ## Missing or Weak Evidence
              {{missing_evidence_list}}

              ## Next Actions (Owners / Dates)
              {{next_actions_table}}

              ## Notes
              {{notes}}

          - path: "PM_SLIDES.md"
            template: |
              # Slide 1 — Title & Hook
              - Product name, one-line value prop
              - Hook: baseline pain and desired outcome

              # Slide 2 — Problem
              - Single-sentence problem
              - Scope, non-goals, baseline metrics

              # Slide 3 — Success
              - North Star + guardrails
              - Measurement plan

              # Slide 4 — Audience
              - Persona & JTBD
              - Top tasks and acceptance criteria
              - Stakeholder RACI (mini)

              # Slide 5 — Solution Overview
              - Before/after flow
              - Where AI intervenes & why
              - Sources: docs/llm-stack-guidance.md; docs/ai_product_management_layers_2025.md

              # Slide 6 — Demo
              - Storyboard frames
              - Trust, control, feedback loop
              - Experiment plan

              # Slide 7 — Infra Diagram
              - Data → Decision → UX
              - Governance overlays, monitoring, rollbacks
              - Sources: docs/llm-stack-guidance.md; docs/ai_product_management_layers_2025.md

              # Slide 8 — Results & Trade-offs
              - Early signals / pilot data
              - Key trade-offs & rationale

              # Slide 9 — Conclusions
              - Risks & mitigations
              - Next steps
              - GTM/enablement plan
